itions\", \"from\": 435, \"to\": 455}, {\"ngram\": \"the other side\", \"from\": 459, \"to\": 473}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 477, \"to\": 486}, {\"ngram\": \"thePacificwaters ofTahiti-\", \"from\": 492, \"to\": 518}, {\"ngram\": \"the strongest reactions\", \"from\": 528, \"to\": 551}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tahitians and others railed against the building of a new viewing tower on Teahupo'o reef because of fears it would hurt marine life.\", \"from\": 554, \"to\": 687, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 554, \"end\": 563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahitians\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9851748506458056e-33, \"text\": \"Tahitians\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahitians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahitians\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 568, \"to\": 574}, {\"ngram\": \"the building\", \"from\": 590, \"to\": 602}, {\"ngram\": \"a new viewing tower\", \"from\": 606, \"to\": 625}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o reef\", \"from\": 629, \"to\": 643}, {\"ngram\": \"fears\", \"from\": 655, \"to\": 660}, {\"ngram\": \"marine life\", \"from\": 675, \"to\": 686}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But organizers say it wasn't just the world-class waves that lured them to the French territory 16,000 kilometers (9,942 miles) away.\", \"from\": 689, \"to\": 822, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 768, \"end\": 774, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.935852198064543, \"rank\": 0.06640565034723671, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"organizers\", \"from\": 693, \"to\": 703}, {\"ngram\": \"just the world-class waves\", \"from\": 718, \"to\": 744}, {\"ngram\": \"9,942 miles\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 815}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris Olympic officials had set an ambitious target of halving their overall carbon footprint compared with the 2012 London and 2016 Rio Games.\", \"from\": 823, \"to\": 966, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 823, \"end\": 828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.239680119467233e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 935, \"end\": 946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999089150192, \"rank\": 9.108502187632054e-08, \"text\": \"2012 London\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an ambitious target\", \"from\": 855, \"to\": 874}, {\"ngram\": \"their overall carbon footprint\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 916}, {\"ngram\": \"2016 Rio Games\", \"from\": 951, \"to\": 965}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tahiti's surfing reef is too far offshore for fans to see the action clearly from the beach, so organizers say they calculated that most would watch on television instead of taking flights, a major source of carbon emissions.\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 1193, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 968, \"end\": 974, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999999997726263, \"rank\": 2.2767691442245223e-10, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 1014, \"to\": 1018}, {\"ngram\": \"the action\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1036}, {\"ngram\": \"the beach\", \"from\": 1050, \"to\": 1059}, {\"ngram\": \"organizers\", \"from\": 1064, \"to\": 1074}, {\"ngram\": \"television\", \"from\": 1120, \"to\": 1130}, {\"ngram\": \"flights\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1156}, {\"ngram\": \"a major source\", \"from\": 1158, \"to\": 1172}, {\"ngram\": \"carbon emissions\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1192}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And fewer spectators, they said, would require little new construction, another key emissions source.\", \"from\": 1195, \"to\": 1296, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fewer spectators\", \"from\": 1199, \"to\": 1215}, {\"ngram\": \"little new construction\", \"from\": 1242, \"to\": 1265}, {\"ngram\": \"another key emissions source\", \"from\": 1267, \"to\": 1295}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We actually did the math,\\\" said Georgina Grenon, director of environmental excellence for the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1405, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1331, \"end\": 1339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgina_River\", \"score\": 0.9999998791354374, \"rank\": 6.298046304385431e-08, \"text\": \"Georgina\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgina_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgina_River\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the math\", \"from\": 1315, \"to\": 1323}, {\"ngram\": \"director\", \"from\": 1348, \"to\": 1356}, {\"ngram\": \"environmental excellence\", \"from\": 1360, \"to\": 1384}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 1389, \"to\": 1404}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There was less impact in Tahiti compared to other metropolitan areas.\\\"\", \"from\": 1406, \"to\": 1477, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1432, \"end\": 1438, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999999997726263, \"rank\": 2.2767691442245223e-10, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"less impact\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1428}, {\"ngram\": \"other metropolitan areas\", \"from\": 1451, \"to\": 1475}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tahiti's selection provides a window into Games organizers' approach to hitting their goal of reducing emissions, the driver of climate change.\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1622, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1479, \"end\": 1485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999999997726263, \"rank\": 2.2767691442245223e-10, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a window\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1515}, {\"ngram\": \"Games organizers' approach\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1547}, {\"ngram\": \"their goal\", \"from\": 1559, \"to\": 1569}, {\"ngram\": \"emissions\", \"from\": 1582, \"to\": 1591}, {\"ngram\": \"the driver\", \"from\": 1593, \"to\": 1603}, {\"ngram\": \"climate change\", \"from\": 1607, \"to\": 1621}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It also underscores an inherent tension in the drive for sustainability: There are tradeoffs, and reducing emissions does not necessarily mean preserving the environment.\", \"from\": 1623, \"to\": 1793, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an inherent tension\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1662}, {\"ngram\": \"the drive\", \"from\": 1666, \"to\": 1675}, {\"ngram\": \"sustainability\", \"from\": 1680, \"to\": 1694}, {\"ngram\": \"tradeoffs\", \"from\": 1706, \"to\": 1715}, {\"ngram\": \"emissions\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 1739}, {\"ngram\": \"the environment\", \"from\": 1777, \"to\": 1792}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers' goal is to limit emissions to 1.58 million metric tons of CO2 equivalent for the July 26-Aug. 11 Games and Paralympics that follow.\", \"from\": 1795, \"to\": 1938, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Organizers' goal\", \"from\": 1795, \"to\": 1811}, {\"ngram\": \"emissions\", \"from\": 1824, \"to\": 1833}, {\"ngram\": \"1.58 million metric tons\", \"from\": 1837, \"to\": 1861}, {\"ngram\": \"CO2\", \"from\": 1865, \"to\": 1868}, {\"ngram\": \"-Aug.\", \"from\": 1895, \"to\": 1900}, {\"ngram\": \"Paralympics\", \"from\": 1914, \"to\": 1925}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's still a lot of pollution - equal to that of about 1.3 million economy passengers flying one way from New York to Paris on Boeing 787 jets, according to myclimate, a climate and sustainability consultancy.\", \"from\": 1939, \"to\": 2150, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2047, \"end\": 2055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999979859987707, \"rank\": 2.0137380542323836e-06, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 2059, \"end\": 2064, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.239680119467233e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2068, \"end\": 2078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boeing_787_Dreamliner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0389671651916105e-43, \"text\": \"Boeing 787\", \"types\": [\"Q11436\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boeing_787_Dreamliner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boeing_787_Dreamliner\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 1952, \"to\": 1957}, {\"ngram\": \"pollution\", \"from\": 1961, \"to\": 1970}, {\"ngram\": \"about 1.3 million economy passengers\", \"from\": 1990, \"to\": 2026}, {\"ngram\": \"one way\", \"from\": 2034, \"to\": 2041}, {\"ngram\": \", a climate and sustainability consultancy\", \"from\": 2107, \"to\": 2149}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a lot less, however, than the footprint of previous Games.\", \"from\": 2152, \"to\": 2215, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the footprint\", \"from\": 2183, \"to\": 2196}, {\"ngram\": \"previous Games\", \"from\": 2200, \"to\": 2214}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers say they are thinking about the Games' future, not just the planet's.\", \"from\": 2217, \"to\": 2297, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Organizers\", \"from\": 2217, \"to\": 2227}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games' future\", \"from\": 2256, \"to\": 2273}, {\"ngram\": \"not just the planet\", \"from\": 2275, \"to\": 2294}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fewer cities are volunteering to spend billions on infrastructure that sometimes falls into disuse.\", \"from\": 2298, \"to\": 2397, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Fewer cities\", \"from\": 2298, \"to\": 2310}, {\"ngram\": \"billions\", \"from\": 2337, \"to\": 2345}, {\"ngram\": \"infrastructure\", \"from\": 2349, \"to\": 2363}, {\"ngram\": \"disuse\", \"from\": 2390, \"to\": 2396}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris and the next host, Los Angeles in 2028, were the only cities left in the race when picked in 2017.\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2502, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2398, \"end\": 2403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.239680119467233e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2423, \"end\": 2434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.6463616701929996, \"rank\": 0.5471209095063054, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the next host\", \"from\": 2408, \"to\": 2421}, {\"ngram\": \"the only cities\", \"from\": 2449, \"to\": 2464}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 2473, \"to\": 2481}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For organizers, hosting less-wasteful Games is key, along with including more inclusive, youth-oriented events such as skateboarding.\", \"from\": 2503, \"to\": 2636, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"organizers\", \"from\": 2507, \"to\": 2517}, {\"ngram\": \"less-wasteful Games\", \"from\": 2527, \"to\": 2546}, {\"ngram\": \"more inclusive, youth-oriented events\", \"from\": 2576, \"to\": 2613}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris is under additional pressure to be a sustainable model: The city hosted the 2015 U.N. climate talks that resulted in the Paris Agreement, the most significant international climate accord to date.\", \"from\": 2638, \"to\": 2840, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2638, \"end\": 2643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.239680119467233e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2725, \"end\": 2729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\", \"score\": 0.9999999992696758, \"rank\": 7.301682077001569e-10, \"text\": \"U.N.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"additional pressure\", \"from\": 2653, \"to\": 2672}, {\"ngram\": \"a sustainable model\", \"from\": 2679, \"to\": 2698}, {\"ngram\": \"The city\", \"from\": 2700, \"to\": 2708}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Agreement\", \"from\": 2761, \"to\": 2780}, {\"ngram\": \"the most significant international climate accord\", \"from\": 2782, \"to\": 2831}, {\"ngram\": \"date\", \"from\": 2835, \"to\": 2839}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Delegates agreed the world should limit average global temperature rise to 2 degrees Celsius (3.6 Fahrenheit) above that of the 1850s, and ideally cap it at 1.5 degrees (2.7 Fahrenheit) - a goal looking increasingly unattainable.\", \"from\": 2841, \"to\": 3070, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3015, \"end\": 3025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fahrenheit\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.927381485094837e-57, \"text\": \"Fahrenheit\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fahrenheit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fahrenheit\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Delegates\", \"from\": 2841, \"to\": 2850}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2858, \"to\": 2867}, {\"ngram\": \"average global temperature rise\", \"from\": 2881, \"to\": 2912}, {\"ngram\": \"2 degrees\", \"from\": 2916, \"to\": 2925}, {\"ngram\": \"Celsius\", \"from\": 2926, \"to\": 2933}, {\"ngram\": \"3.6 Fahrenheit\", \"from\": 2935, \"to\": 2949}, {\"ngram\": \"1.5 degrees\", \"from\": 2998, \"to\": 3009}, {\"ngram\": \"a goal\", \"from\": 3029, \"to\": 3035}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Independent experts say Paris appears to be decarbonizing in the systematic ways businesses do: Calculate total emissions, then start cutting, including myriad small CO2 savings that add up significantly.\", \"from\": 3072, \"to\": 3276, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3096, \"end\": 3101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.239680119467233e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Independent experts\", \"from\": 3072, \"to\": 3091}, {\"ngram\": \"the systematic ways\", \"from\": 3133, \"to\": 3152}, {\"ngram\": \"businesses\", \"from\": 3153, \"to\": 3163}, {\"ngram\": \"total emissions\", \"from\": 3178, \"to\": 3193}, {\"ngram\": \"myriad small CO2 savings\", \"from\": 3225, \"to\": 3249}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers targeted reductions across three categories: construction, transportation and operations.\", \"from\": 3277, \"to\": 3377, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Organizers\", \"from\": 3277, \"to\": 3287}, {\"ngram\": \"reductions\", \"from\": 3297, \"to\": 3307}, {\"ngram\": \"three categories\", \"from\": 3315, \"to\": 3331}, {\"ngram\": \"construction\", \"from\": 3333, \"to\": 3345}, {\"ngram\": \"transportation\", \"from\": 3347, \"to\": 3361}, {\"ngram\": \"operations\", \"from\": 3366, \"to\": 3376}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They seem to be taking a very thoughtful approach,\\\" said Adam Braun of Clarasight, which builds carbon-planning software for companies.\", \"from\": 3379, \"to\": 3515, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3442, \"end\": 3447, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scooter_Braun\", \"score\": 0.9999999988640411, \"rank\": 1.0033859755507273e-09, \"text\": \"Braun\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scooter_Braun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scooter_Braun\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a very thoughtful approach\", \"from\": 3403, \"to\": 3429}, {\"ngram\": \"Clarasight\", \"from\": 3451, \"to\": 3461}, {\"ngram\": \"carbon-planning software\", \"from\": 3476, \"to\": 3500}, {\"ngram\": \"companies\", \"from\": 3505, \"to\": 3514}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They are trying to do something that is indicative of how many organizations will be holding themselves accountable.\\\"\", \"from\": 3516, \"to\": 3634, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 3539, \"to\": 3548}, {\"ngram\": \"how many organizations\", \"from\": 3571, \"to\": 3593}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The biggest break from previous Games is in construction.\", \"from\": 3636, \"to\": 3693, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The biggest break\", \"from\": 3636, \"to\": 3653}, {\"ngram\": \"previous Games\", \"from\": 3659, \"to\": 3673}, {\"ngram\": \"construction\", \"from\": 3680, \"to\": 3692}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers say 95% of facilities are existing or will be temporary.\", \"from\": 3694, \"to\": 3761, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Organizers\", \"from\": 3694, \"to\": 3704}, {\"ngram\": \"95%\", \"from\": 3709, \"to\": 3712}, {\"ngram\": \"facilities\", \"from\": 3716, \"to\": 3726}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two new structures were deemed unavoidable: The Olympic Village, to house athletes and later become housing and office space, and the aquatics center in Paris' disadvantaged northern suburbs.\", \"from\": 3762, \"to\": 3953, \"en